org.pepstock.charba.client.data

Class LineDataset

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.commons.NativeObjectContainer
      • org.pepstock.charba.client.data.Dataset
        • org.pepstock.charba.client.data.LiningDataset
          • org.pepstock.charba.client.data.LineDataset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasDataPoints, HasDataset, HasPointFillStrokeStyles, HasFill
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ScatterDataset, StackedAreaDataset, TimeSeriesLineDataset

    public class LineDataset
extends LiningDataset
implements HasDataPoints
    The line chart allows a number of properties to be specified for each dataset. These are used to set display properties for a specific dataset.
    All point* properties can be specified as an array. If these are set to an array value, the first value applies to the first point, the second value to the second point, and so on.
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero

      • setCubicInterpolationMode

        public void setCubicInterpolationMode(CubicInterpolationMode mode)
        Sets algorithm used to interpolate a smooth curve from the discrete data points.
        The following interpolation modes are supported:

         'default'
 'monotone'

        The 'default' algorithm uses a custom weighted cubic interpolation, which produces pleasant curves for all types of datasets.
        The 'monotone' algorithm is more suited to y = f(x) datasets : it preserves monotonicity (or piecewise monotonicity) of the dataset being interpolated, and ensures local extremums (if any) stay at input data points.
        Parameters:
        mode - algorithm used to interpolate a smooth curve from the discrete data points

      • getClip

        public double getClip()
        Returns how to clip relative to chartArea.
        Positive value allows overflow, negative value clips that many pixels inside chartArea. 0 = clip at chartArea.
        If the clip was set by a Clip object, returns UndefinedValues.DOUBLE.
        Returns:
        positive value allows overflow, negative value clips that many pixels inside chartArea. 0 = clip at chartArea.
        If the clip was set by a Clip object, returns UndefinedValues.DOUBLE

      • getClipAsObject

        public Clip getClipAsObject()
        Returns how to clip relative to chartArea.
        Positive value allows overflow, negative value clips that many pixels inside chartArea. 0 = clip at chartArea.
        If the clip was NOT set by a Clip object, returns a Clip instance with the same values.
        Returns:
        clip positive value allows overflow, negative value clips that many pixels inside chartArea. 0 = clip at chartArea.
        If the clip was NOT set by a Clip object, returns a Clip instance with the same values.
